                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.3335/91a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-19T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 19, 1940—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>114. From the Under Secretary. Following her visit to Rio de Janeiro on June 26
                    it is proposed to send the USS <hi rend="italic">Wichita</hi> to Montevideo for
                    a 5–day visit. Please telegraph me if you think it advisable that the <hi
                        rend="italic">Wichita</hi> should, after the termination of her stay in
                    Montevideo, visit some Argentine port, and if so the number of days this visit
                    should comprise. [Welles.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
